            <div class=3D"sidebar">
        =20
                <div class=3D"additional-info">
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-1" data-index=3D"1" class=3D=
"additional-container first">
                            <b>The scene where Anya saves B.J. in The New C=
olossus is primarily notable because she did it topless, pregnant, and cove=
red in blood. If there=E2=80=99s ever been a more cathartic image than this=
 in a video game, I don=E2=80=99t want to know about it.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-2" data-index=3D"2" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>For all the gonzo humor present in the reboo=
ted Wolfenstein series, it=E2=80=99s also very dark. Wolfenstein 2 might st=
art at one of its darkest points when arch-nemesis Frau Engel murders B.J.=
=E2=80=99s close ally and friend Caroline Becker. But it=E2=80=99s not a qu=
ick death for Becker. Engel first tries to force her own daughter to execut=
e the paralyzed Engel before doing the deed herself. And she immediately fo=
llows up the gruesome scene by torturing B.J. psychologically with Becker=
=E2=80=99s death. Executions don=E2=80=99t get darker, or crazier than this=
.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-3" data-index=3D"3" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>There are action set pieces, and then there =
is fighting a wave of robots and Nazis while falling from the sky in your c=
hildhood home. One of the narratives in Wolfenstein The New Colossus is how=
 B.J. tackles this traumatic childhood. And when he finally confronts his a=
busive father in his old house, the developers decided to use the emotional=
ly charged moment to stage one of the most intense and batsh*t crazy gamepl=
ay moments in the entire series.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-4" data-index=3D"4" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                           =20
                           =20
                            <p>Advertisement</p>
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-5" data-index=3D"5" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>MachineGames loves to tear down hero B.J. Bl=
azkowicz any chance they get. When the events of Wolfenstein 2: The New Col=
ossus begins, B.J. is still dealing with the repercussions of his fight wit=
h Deathshead, in that he wakes up with a severely weakened body. When the N=
azis invade the U-Boat B.J. is on, he has no choice but to mow them down wh=
ilst bound to a wheelchair. It=E2=80=99s a frantic, exhilarating opening th=
at sets the tone for Wolfenstein 2=E2=80=99s increasingly crazy moments.</b=
>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-6" data-index=3D"6" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>I=E2=80=99m not sure there=E2=80=99s ever be=
en a more repulsive character in the rebooted Wolfenstein series than Hitle=
r, which is fitting of course, as he was an incredibly repulsive man in rea=
l life. Nonetheless, that didn=E2=80=99t make his pissing, puking, murderin=
g actions in the New Colossus any less disturbing.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-7" data-index=3D"7" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>Engel is a villain you just love to hate. Th=
at=E2=80=99s why it feels so good to see her get decked by a giant robot, w=
hilst she=E2=80=99s trying to execute B.J. via firing squad in The New Orde=
r. What=E2=80=99s crazy is not only does she survive a robot fist to the fa=
ce, but she=E2=80=99s still willing to get face-to-face with B.J. to taunt =
him, smushed face and all.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-8" data-index=3D"8" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                           =20
                           =20
                            <p>Advertisement</p>
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-9" data-index=3D"9" class=3D=
"additional-container">
                            <b>Frau Engel doesn=E2=80=99t wait too long to =
pay B.J. and the resistance back for the whole smushed face incident, as wh=
ile B.J. is off stealing nuclear launch codes on the moon, Engel locates th=
e resistance base in Berlin and nearly cripple them by killing or capturing=
 most of B.J.=E2=80=99s friends. It was surprising, led to the deaths of ma=
jor characters like Klaus and Tekla, and it perfectly set the stage for the=
 climax of New Order.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-10" data-index=3D"10" class=
=3D"additional-container">
                            <b>In Wolfenstein: The New Order, antagonist De=
athshead asks you to choose which one of your comrades, Fergus or Wyatt, he=
 should kill. It=E2=80=99s a horrific Sophie=E2=80=99s choice, made worse b=
y the incredibly disgusting way in which Deathshead murders whatever poor s=
oul you sacrifice. </b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-11" data-index=3D"11" class=
=3D"additional-container">
                            <b>In a scene that could only be described as =
=E2=80=98graphic=E2=80=99 in a game so already soaked in gore, Deathshead d=
rills a hole into Wyatt or Fergus' brain and sucks it out into a tube. Late=
r on in The New Order Deathshead reveals he put the brain into the head of =
a robot, which eventually tries to kill you, and then later begs for the sw=
eet release of death. What a torturous way to go.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-12" data-index=3D"12" class=
=3D"additional-container">
                           =20
                           =20
                            <p>Advertisement</p>
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-13" data-index=3D"13" class=
=3D"additional-container">
                            <b> B.J. Blazkowicz straight-up died in Wolfens=
tein The New Colossus, and it was the best moment in the whole game. For mo=
st of the first half of The New Colossus, B.J. was in dire straits. Weakene=
d from his fight at the end of Wolfenstein: The New Order, B.J. spent much =
of the game on life support. So how did he end up recovering in time to lib=
erate America from the Nazis? By getting beheaded in a publicly televised e=
xecution, only for his friends to quickly steal B.J.=E2=80=99s decapitated =
head and surgically attach it to the body of a Nazi super-soldier. Weird fl=
ex, but okay.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                    <div id=3D"additional-info-14" data-index=3D"14" class=
=3D"additional-container last active">
                            <b>New Colossus ends without a big final battle=
 against a notable villain, which would be kind of a disappointment, if not=
 for the fact that right after the big final battle, you and your crew inte=
rrupt a national late night interview with Frau Engel to deliver her exactl=
y what she deserves, a hatchet through her evil Nazi skull. It=E2=80=99s on=
e of the most graphic =E2=80=9Choly shit=E2=80=9D moments of the series, bu=
t also strangely one of the most feel-good moments as well.</b>
                           =20
                           =20
                           =20
                        </div>
                   =20
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

