                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"9">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sm.ign.com/t/ign_ap/screenshot/=
f/frau-engel/frau-engel-doesnt-wait-too-long-to-pay-bj-and-the-resistance_h=
y5s.200.png" alt=3D"Frau Engel doesn=E2=80=99t wait too long to pay B.J. an=
d the resistance back for the whole smushed face incident, as while B.J. is=
 off stealing nuclear launch codes on the moon, Engel locates the resistanc=
e base in Berlin and nearly cripple them by killing or capturing most of B.=
J.=E2=80=99s friends. It was surprising, led to the deaths of major charact=
ers like Klaus and Tekla, and it perfectly set the stage for the climax of =
New Order." class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"10">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sm.ign.com/t/ign_ap/screenshot/=
i/in-wolfens/in-wolfenstein-the-new-order-antagonist-deathshead-asks-you_51=
up.200.jpg" alt=3D"In Wolfenstein: The New Order, antagonist Deathshead ask=
s you to choose which one of your comrades, Fergus or Wyatt, he should kill=
. It=E2=80=99s a horrific Sophie=E2=80=99s choice, made worse by the incred=
ibly disgusting way in which Deathshead murders whatever poor soul you sacr=
ifice. " class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"11">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sm.ign.com/t/ign_ap/screenshot/=
i/in-a-scene/in-a-scene-that-could-only-be-described-as-graphic-in-a-game_k=
zyv.200.png" alt=3D"In a scene that could only be described as =E2=80=98gra=
phic=E2=80=99 in a game so already soaked in gore, Deathshead drills a hole=
 into Wyatt or Fergus' brain and sucks it out into a tube. Later on in The =
New Order Deathshead reveals he put the brain into the head of a robot, whi=
ch eventually tries to kill you, and then later begs for the sweet release =
of death. What a torturous way to go." class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"12">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sea.ign.com/switch/152123/None"=
 alt=3D"{'advertising_slide': True}" class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"13">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sm.ign.com/t/ign_ap/screenshot/=
b/bj-blazkow/bj-blazkowicz-straight-up-died-in-wolfenstein-the-new-coloss_6=
hdj.200.png" alt=3D" B.J. Blazkowicz straight-up died in Wolfenstein The Ne=
w Colossus, and it was the best moment in the whole game. For most of the f=
irst half of The New Colossus, B.J. was in dire straits. Weakened from his =
fight at the end of Wolfenstein: The New Order, B.J. spent much of the game=
 on life support. So how did he end up recovering in time to liberate Ameri=
ca from the Nazis? By getting beheaded in a publicly televised execution, o=
nly for his friends to quickly steal B.J.=E2=80=99s decapitated head and su=
rgically attach it to the body of a Nazi super-soldier. Weird flex, but oka=
y." class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
                <button class=3D"mini-thumb" aria-label=3D"View Image" data=
-index=3D"14">
                    <div class=3D"slide-wrapper">
                        <img src=3D"https://sm.ign.com/t/ign_ap/screenshot/=
n/new-coloss/new-colossus-ends-without-a-big-final-battle-against-a-notab_h=
p7d.200.png" alt=3D"New Colossus ends without a big final battle against a =
notable villain, which would be kind of a disappointment, if not for the fa=
ct that right after the big final battle, you and your crew interrupt a nat=
ional late night interview with Frau Engel to deliver her exactly what she =
deserves, a hatchet through her evil Nazi skull. It=E2=80=99s one of the mo=
st graphic =E2=80=9Choly shit=E2=80=9D moments of the series, but also stra=
ngely one of the most feel-good moments as well." class=3D"gallery-image">
                    </div>
                </button>
               =20
            </div>
         =20
        </div>
